          <p class="lead">How did they survive?</p>
  
          <p>In 1962, the Anglin brothers and Frank Morris escaped from Alcatraz, a federal island prison built on the coast of San Francisco.</p>
  
          <p>The men escaped the prison using sharpened spoons and the island on a makeshift raft of 50 raincoats.</p>
  
          <p>The waters around the island were dangerous for the men on the raft and their likelihood of survival was extremely low.</p>
  
          <p>After 17 years of searching for the missing bodies of the Alcatraz escapees, on December 31, 1979, the San Francisco Police Department closed the case on the missing inmates. The escape from Alcatraz will forever remain unsolved.</p>
  
